**Total: 52 rules × 4 cases = 208 boundary test cases**

Cross-Stream Discoveries

**CROSS-STREAM:** S2 (Rules): RULE-ROUNDING test cases depend on
Q-CALC-01 resolution. Until DERP confirms rounding methodology, both
banker\'s rounding and standard rounding should be tested. The YAML rule
definition for RULE-ROUNDING should include both variants with a
governance flag indicating which is active.

**CROSS-STREAM:** S2 (Rules): RULE-SVC-EARNED partial-year calculation
(Q-CALC-02) affects boundary precision for RULE-RULE-OF-75 and
RULE-RULE-OF-85. A member at sum = 74.99 under year-month method might
be 75.01 under exact-day method. Both methods should be implemented with
a configuration switch.

**CROSS-STREAM:** S1 (Data): DQ-006 tier misclassification detection
requires the MEMBER_MASTER table to include both TIER_CD and HIRE_DT
columns. The schema must support computed-vs-stored tier comparison.

**CROSS-STREAM:** S3 (API): Integration test contracts define exact JSON
response shapes that the API spec must match. The
RetirementCalculationResponse must include a Trace section with rule
references --- this is a Phase 1 Transparent requirement, not optional.

**CROSS-STREAM:** S4 (UX): Workspace composition tests verify that
ScenarioModeler appears for early retirement cases. The component
definition in S4 must include a \'threshold proximity\' data requirement
that shows how close the member is to the next eligibility tier.

**CROSS-STREAM:** S2 (Rules): The full statutory reduction tables
(RULE-EARLY-REDUCE-T12 and RULE-EARLY-REDUCE-T3) must be implemented as
lookup tables, NOT as formulas per CRITICAL-001 resolution. Test cases
verify every integer age from minimum to 64.

**CROSS-STREAM:** S1 (Data): DQ-005 (incorrect benefit payments)
requires the full calculation engine to detect. This creates a circular
dependency: the engine must be built before this data quality check can
run. BUILD_PLAN should schedule DQ-005 detection after the calculation
engine is operational (Day 5+).
